	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f100495914111272>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=14&mid=100495914111272>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=100495914111272>RE: nec</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=100495914111272#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Nov 5th 6:19 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=49677><span id=Guru>alaaraaf the Puissant</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>179 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.93]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Hey.<br><br>If you're solo'ing with the pet and it does all the damage, you should get 50% of the EXP.&nbsp;&nbsp;The pet gets the other half.  Essentially, if the pet does more damage than you, it takes 50%.  If you do more damage, it takes about 1%.<br><br>If you're in a group, this is a little different.  The pet should be taking a flat rate 1% of the group's EXP.  (It'd be pretty sad if the pet was out damaging the whole group anyhow.)  <br><br>HOWEVER...<br><br>If you are in a group and you do nothing, you will be awarded with no EXP.  I don't know, (because I have never tested this part,) but I would guess that if you do nothing but send in the pet, this probably still stands.<br><br>The other thing to consider is that creatures are not all the same level.  So, if you are hunting something that is at the bottom end of the creatures that will give you EXP, you won't necessarilly always get EXP.  For example, at L41, stalag terrors mostly still give EXP.  But, the lowest level ones don't.  So, every so often you kill one that gives nothing.<br><br>Hope that helps.<br><br>AlAaraaf.<br>"Death is coming..."</p>&nbsp;<br>"Te aurdire no possum. Musa sapienum fixa est in aura."</td></td></tr>
