	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=43653><span id=Scholar>GLASS</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>202 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [1.80]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Alaaraaf,<br><br>You can be in a group and do absolutely nothing throughout an entire fight and still get your even split of xp.&nbsp;&nbsp;The only exception I can think of is if you are out of range (i.e. you are all the way across the zone or in a different zone) when the group kills something, then you will not get xp.<br><br>To the original poster,<br><br>If you are hunting monsters that your pet can solo without any help from you, then they are most likely green cons and too low to give you any xp.  Try hunting something a little tougher and see if the experience starts coming in.<br><br>-Yizzelar</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
