<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f100463704892196>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=14&mid=100463704892196>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=100463704892196>3 Nec Soloing Techniques</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=100463704892196#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Nov 1st 12:50 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>When i hit 22 i was in LOIO and a friend and i decided to play around with several new soloing techniques (we did these w/ all 1 lvl blues)... here's what i found:<br><br>1) fear kiting... the classic<br>cast your darkness at the mob (warning: darkness is resisted quite a bit but not often by blues).&nbsp;&nbsp;the mob will run at you and while he does cast your biggest dot at him, probably the heat blood series.  the mob should be almost to you by this time and now you pet attack.  while pets tanking cast fear.  follow this with one more dot if necessary and follow the mob to watch for adds and avoid wandering mobs.  re-fear/darkness as necessary, though darkness shouldn't be a problem.  rinse repeat.  i was able to kill 4 mobs/mana bar and sometimes 5 if nothing resisted.  this works all the way up to 50 and maybe even 60 just use the upgraded versions of all the previous spells and add dots as necessary.<br><br>2) charm killing<br>this only works if you have the undead charm spells and there is undead nearby obviously.  in loio i used charbone skellies (they hit hard) you need to have a DD up for this to work, and since you can't do this w/ a pet MAKE SURE you have a sow, i can't stress that enough.  what you do is find a undead and charm it.  then go to another mob and aggro it, as soon as it hits you your new friend will attack it and they will fight.  you'll probably need to help your friend kill the mob so just lifetap it a time or 2. the charm will probably break shortly after the fight and as soon as your friend becomes unfriendly kill it.  this should be easy as it will probably be almost dead from the previous fight.  this is a very dangerous way of fighting because if your charm breaks early or doesn't stick at all you have one very pissed off hard hitting skelli on you ass... thats where sow comes in.  but if you do it right its 2 kills w/ very little effort on your part.  <br><br>3)  Pet tanking<br>this works on any blues the lower the better actually (that you can still get xp on of course).  the strategy is to cast pets till you get the best one you can.  then make sure you have these spells up:  spirit armor, pet buff, pet heal, allure of death, and leach... and 3 others, preferably lifetap... but whatever they don't matter much.  you pull w/ a baby dot and then just sick your pet on the mob.  use /pet health report and have allure and leach on.  heal your pet whenever you need to.  don't fear or dot, just sit there and let the pet tank the mob.  note: this doesn't work well w/ animals since they tend to hit very hard ie. sabertooth cats et al. but works great w/ gobo's and sarnaks)  if you need to help a bit by lifetapping or poison bolting but let the pet do most of the work and save your mana for healing it.  i was able to kill a record (for me anyways) 7 mobs on one mana bar before i was oom and had to med, and my pet (who lived) had to sit and heal.  rinse repeat.  <br><br>just thought i'd share some of my experiences w/ ppl and new nec's who can always use some advice.  fear kiting (number 1) is by far my favorite and prolly the safest way to solo.<br><br>oh yeah one more piece of advice almost any nec can tell you:  NEVER EVER under any circumstances take feign death out of your spell bar.  i took it out once to cast a pet for like 30 seconds and in that time  got killed by a wandering mob.  since then it hasn't left my spell list.  <br><br>Hope this helps somebody or at least gets ppl to try some new things =)<br><br>Spyrall Bloodstayne<br>30th Necromancer<br>Ayonae Ro </p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
