	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=14&mid=100412770423086>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=100412770423086>Melee Necros</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=100412770423086#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Oct 26th 4:21 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=112146><span id= >CzarOfCard</span></a><br><span id=notbold>3 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I am a twinked Necro, but have a very good strategy for working on your weapons skills.&nbsp;&nbsp;Besides the fear kiting strategy (Darkness-pet attack-fear-beat them as they run), another is using the leach spell.  You get it at 12th level, and is a DOT that gives you around 70 hp back.  Basically cast darkness, leach, and then weigh in with your trusty weapon.  Make sure to use your pet, who can cover your butt if you have to pull back.  The mobs will beat on you, but you will take no damage while the spell lasts, unless they start hitting you for 20 points a shot on a consistent basis.  Make sure you have an AC around 300, or you will be hit around the dungeon like a croquet ball.  I'm 19th, and my 1 handed pierce is around 63.  Helps out a lot when my pet drops, and I have to really solo.  You can get in about 50-60 points yourself when the mob is running in fear, making life easier on your pet.  An extra 12 points here and there is much better than "Miss, miss miss!"  <br><br>Ozadar<br>Order of the 19th Circle</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
