	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=14&mid=10049406143331>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=10049406143331>RE: do pets lvl up</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=10049406143331#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Nov 5th 1:10 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Contrary to popular belief, your pet actually DOES level up.&nbsp;&nbsp;I have had a pet con green to me, and after fighting a lot (I let him do most of the killing while I keep my mana up) he conned blue to me.  I have read on numerous other strat guides that they DO in fact gain exp.  The proof of this, is if your pet does the KILLING blow on a mob, then he takes a percentage of the exp, you will notice that your exp bar will NOT go up as much when HE kills the same mob that same mob would give you had YOU killed it.<br><br>Your pet does gain exp, and he does level, but its not worth it.  Its pretty much a pointless feature because, A: you should have a "stop" button for your pet <br><br>(my stop button fills up all five lines: /pet back off /pause 5 /pet back off /pause 5 /pet back off)<br><br>This will prevent your pet from stealing your exp, as it is not worth the exp loss just to get him to the next level.  Chances are you will log, or he will die before he actually DOES level, so I wouldn't even think about letting him take the kills.<br><br>Skildoroth<br>Iksar Necromancer<br>Level 30<br>Sarryn</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
