	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=85776><span id=Sage>Cannis the Mighty</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>690 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.19]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I don't know if your a twink or what your experience is in EQ.&nbsp;&nbsp;But as a 6th level necro you have the basic spells that will be your staple all the way up to 60th level. The rest of your spells will be icing on the cake. But fear kiting will be your most valuable soloing tool.<br><br>Send your pet in to attack cast Clinging Darkness Damage over time and slows target movement. Then cast Fear-Single Target Fear Spell (18 Secs). Then you go in and attack and reapply fear and darkeness again. <br><br>Remember to every once and while attack mobs too cuz that will bring up your defenses.<br><br>You should be able to solo yellow con mobs with no problem depending though, on if you have room to fear kite.  If you don't have room to fear kite then you can send you pet in, cast DoT's then you tank along with your pet and step back and life tap.<br><br>I hope this helps and I am sure others can add some useful hints as well.<br> <br><br></p>&nbsp;<br>Cannis 65th Ranger<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69645" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69645</a> <br><br></td></td></tr>
